Defers invoking the function until the current call stack has 
cleared,similar to using setTimeout with a delay of 0. Useful 
for performingexpensive computations or HTML rendering in chunks without blocking 
the UI threadfrom updating. If you pass the optional arguments, 
they will beforwarded on to the function when it is 
invoked. */
